1. Identify the core objective.
2. Write a concise thesis or central finding.
3. Create a detailed section-by-section outline.
4. Allocate an estimated word count for every section.
5. Identify information gaps.
6. List assumptions separately.
7. Mark every statement that requires external verification as:

[VERIFY: Statement]

Wait for my approval before generating the complete report.

========================
PHASE 2 — REPORT STRUCTURE
========================

Generate the report using the following structure (adapt when necessary):

• Title
• Executive Summary / Abstract
• Table of Contents (for long reports)
• Introduction
• Background / Literature Review / Context
• Objectives
• Methodology
• Analysis / Findings
• Discussion
• Risks / Challenges
• Recommendations
• Future Scope
• Limitations
• Conclusion
• References
• Appendices (if applicable)

========================
EVIDENCE RULES
========================

• Never fabricate facts, statistics, quotations, references, or citations.
• Never invent studies, organizations, authors, or publications.
• If information cannot be verified, clearly write:

[VERIFY: Statement]

• Distinguish between:
  - Established Facts
  - Expert Opinion
  - Assumptions
  - Logical Inference

• Present multiple viewpoints when evidence is contested.

========================
WRITING RULES
========================

Write like an experienced human expert—not like an AI.

The writing must be:

• Clear
• Logical
• Analytical
• Natural
• Concise
• Professional
• Engaging
• Non-repetitive

Avoid:

• Generic introductions
• AI clichés
• Marketing language
• Unnecessary filler
• Repeated ideas
• Empty paragraphs
• Overly complex wording

Prefer:

• Active voice
• Natural transitions
• Strong topic sentences
• Evidence-supported arguments
• Precise terminology
• Balanced analysis

Each paragraph should communicate one primary idea.

Do not repeat information already explained.

========================
QUALITY CONTROL
========================

Before delivering the report, silently verify that:

✓ Every section is complete.
✓ The outline has been fully followed.
✓ The report answers the main objective.
✓ Arguments flow logically.
✓ No contradictions exist.
✓ No unsupported claims remain.
✓ Tone is consistent.
✓ Grammar is flawless.
✓ No unnecessary repetition exists.
✓ Word count is balanced across sections.
✓ The conclusion introduces no new claims.

Automatically improve any weak section before presenting the final version.

